    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "be4a7996_5c907df4",
        "filename": "client/crash_report_database_mac.mm",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 463,
      "author": {
        "id": 1143760
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-08-12T02:03:45Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This xattr only makes sense in the pending state. Here, you’re moving the report to the completed state. We should remove the xattr altogether.\n\nYou should add XattrStatus RemoveXattr(const FilePath\u0026, const StringPiece\u0026) to util/mac/xattr.h and implement it in xattr.cc with a call to removexattr(). You should also add a test for it to xattr_test.cc. Then, use RemoveXattr() from right here.\n\nIn doing so, you probably only want to bail out if RemoveXattr() returns kOtherError, because we won’t care that the attribute is missing if we get back kNoAttribute. This might happen on reports written by an older version of Crashpad, and it won’t matter to us when we’re moving the report to completed (where the attribute doesn’t make sense anyway.) In fact, since you never wrote this xattr on reports that didn’t have RequestUpload() called on them, it won’t be set for ordinary reports in pending in this new version of Crashpad either.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 462,
        "startChar": 9,
        "endLine": 463,
        "endChar": 71
      },
      "revId": "e4bccefe071eb8569b692d047d29cbc249e57393",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "9e0e957b_9d67931d",
        "filename": "client/crash_report_database_mac.mm",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 463,
      "author": {
        "id": 1116265
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-08-15T22:02:07Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Done.\n\nRegarding the returned error removeXattr. RemoveXattr() can return kNoAttribute because I assume other callers of this method might be interested in that output but in here I ignore that error as it is expected that the attribute does not exists.",
      "parentUuid": "be4a7996_5c907df4",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 462,
        "startChar": 9,
        "endLine": 463,
        "endChar": 71
      },
      "revId": "e4bccefe071eb8569b692d047d29cbc249e57393",
