      "message": "\u003e Done.\n\u003e \n\u003e Regarding the returned error removeXattr. RemoveXattr() can return kNoAttribute because I\n\u003e assume other callers of this method might be interested in that output but in here I ignore\n\u003e that error as it is expected that the attribute does not exists.\n\nThat’s correct, that’s what I intended (I wrote “you probably only want to bail out if RemoveXattr() returns kOtherError, because we won’t care that the attribute is missing if we get back kNoAttribute.”)",
      "parentUuid": "9e0e957b_9d67931d",
