        "id": 1143760
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-08-12T02:03:45Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This test is a good start. However, you should also test:\n - that the UUIDs in pending at this point are report_0_uuid and report_1_uuid (beware that you may not get them back in that order, though)\n - that report_1 does have the upload-explicitly-requested bit set\n - that report_0 does NOT have this bit set.\n\nThen, you should RequestUpload() on something that’s already in pending, because that should work too, so RequestUpload on report_0_uuid, grab the pending reports again, and make sure that the upload-explicitly-requested bit HAS been set. You should also check that setting the bit on a pending report that already has the bit set works, too.\n\nYou should also be checking that the file path that’s claimed for the report actually exists after calling RequestUpload(), since some databases are supposed to move it around. You may wind up writing a bunch of similar LookUpCrashReport() code repeatedly, so it may make sense to put your RequestUpload() call for testing purposes into a wrapper on the test fixture class in the same fashion as CrashReportDatabaseTest::CreateCrashReport() and CrashReportDatabaseTest::UploadReport().\n\nFinally, it’s important to check that a report that has already been uploaded does not qualify for RequestUpload() and that instead, RequestUpload() returns your special new error code.",
      "revId": "e4bccefe071eb8569b692d047d29cbc249e57393",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
